''[[The Boys (TV series)|The Boys]]'' is an American [[Satire (film and television)|satirical]] [[Superhero fiction|superhero]] television series, developed by showrunner [[Eric Kripke]] for [[Amazon Prime Video]], that premiered on July 26, 2019. Based on the [[The Boys (comics)|comic book of the same name]] by [[Garth Ennis]] and [[Darick Robertson]], it follows the eponymous team of [[Vigilantism|vigilantes]] as they attempt to take down The Seven, a team of [[Superpower (ability)|superpowered]] individuals who abuse their powers.

Originally intended to be a [[Feature film|feature-length film]] [[trilogy]], the comic book series adaptation began its development in 2008 with [[Adam McKay]] set to direct, until a series of creative differences led to the project's cancellation until it was revived in 2016 as a television series.<ref>{{cite web |last=Writer |first=Guest |date=February 13, 2012 |title='The Boys' Movie No Longer in Development at Columbia |url=https://whatculture.com/film/the-boys-movie-no-longer-in-development-at-columbia |access-date=August 6, 2024 |publisher=[[WhatCulture]] |archive-date=December 14, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231214190913/https://whatculture.com/film/the-boys-movie-no-longer-in-development-at-columbia |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.indiewire.com/news/general-news/adam-mckay-the-boys-film-trilogy-1235019798/ |title=Adam McKay Wrote a 'The Boys' Screenplay in 2008: Comic Book Creator Says Hollywood Wasn't 'Ready' for Satirical Superheroes |last=Bergeson |first=Samantha |publisher=[[IndieWire]] |date=June 25, 2024 |access-date=August 6, 2024}}</ref><ref name="Cinemax">{{cite web |last=Andreeva |first=Nellie |date=April 6, 2016 |title='The Boys' Drama Based on Comic Book Set at Cinemax with Seth Rogen, Evan Goldberg, Eric Kripke, Original Film & Sony |url=https://deadline.com/2016/04/the-boys-drama-series-comic-book-cinemax-seth-rogen-evan-goldberg-eric-kripke-original-film-sony-1201732097/ |access-date=August 6, 2024 |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |archive-date=February 19, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180219035113/http://deadline.com/2016/04/the-boys-drama-series-comic-book-cinemax-seth-rogen-evan-goldberg-eric-kripke-original-film-sony-1201732097/ |url-status=live}}</ref> The series premiered on July 26, 2019, on [[Amazon Prime Video]]. Kripke also serves as an [[executive producer]], alongside [[Seth Rogen]] and [[Evan Goldberg]].<ref name="Cinemax"/><ref>{{cite web |last=Andreeva |first=Nellie |date=November 8, 2017 |title=Amazon Orders 'The Boys' Superhero Drama Series Based on Comic from Eric Kripke, Evan Goldberg & Seth Rogen |url=https://deadline.com/2017/11/amazon-the-boys-superhero-drama-series-eric-kripke-evan-goldberg-seth-rogen-1202204073/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201129184433/https://deadline.com/2017/11/amazon-the-boys-superhero-drama-series-eric-kripke-evan-goldberg-seth-rogen-1202204073/ |archive-date=November 29, 2020 |access-date=August 6, 2024 |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Turchiano |first=Danielle |date=November 8, 2017 |title=Amazon Greenlights Eric Kripke's Superhero Drama 'The Boys' |url=https://variety.com/2017/tv/news/amazon-eric-kripke-the-boys-evan-goldberg-seth-rogen-1202610061/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180831035614/https://variety.com/2017/tv/news/amazon-eric-kripke-the-boys-evan-goldberg-seth-rogen-1202610061/ |archive-date=August 31, 2018 |access-date=August 6, 2024 |website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Radish |first=Christina |date=September 26, 2019 |title=Eric Kripke on Amazon's 'The Boys' and the End of 'Supernatural' |url=https://collider.com/the-boys-eric-kripke-interview/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230314204513/https://collider.com/the-boys-eric-kripke-interview/ |archive-date=March 14, 2023 |access-date=August 6, 2024 |website=[[Collider (website)|Collider]]}}</ref> Filming for the series takes place in Canada despite the storyline primarily taking place in New York City.<ref>{{cite web |last=Watson |first=Fay |date=July 26, 2019 |title='The Boys' on Amazon location: Where is 'The Boys' filmed? Where's it set? |url=https://www.express.co.uk/showbiz/tv-radio/1157369/The-Boys-Amazon-Prime-location-Where-is-The-Boys-filmed-Where-is-it-set-series |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220421193333/https://www.express.co.uk/showbiz/tv-radio/1157369/The-Boys-Amazon-Prime-location-Where-is-The-Boys-filmed-Where-is-it-set-series |archive-date=April 21, 2022 |access-date=August 6, 2024 |website=[[Daily Express|Express]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Moon |first=Ra |title=Where was 'The Boys' Filmed? Guide to All the Filming Locations |url=https://www.atlasofwonders.com/2019/07/the-boys-filming-locations-toronto.html |access-date=August 6, 2024 |website=Atlas of Wonders |archive-date=June 12, 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210612022204/https://www.atlasofwonders.com/2019/07/the-boys-filming-locations-toronto.html |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Shinuda |first=Jonah |date=November 8, 2020 |title=Did you know Prime's biggest TV series 'The Boys' was partially filmed in Mississauga? |url=https://www.insauga.com/did-you-know-primes-biggest-tv-series-the-boys-was-partially-filmed-in-mississauga/ |access-date=August 6, 2024 |website=Insauga |archive-date=June 12, 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210612022200/https://www.insauga.com/did-you-know-primes-biggest-tv-series-the-boys-was-partially-filmed-in-mississauga |url-status=live}}</ref> With the exception of the [[The Boys season 1|first season]], which released every episode on the same day,<ref>{{cite web |last1=Gemmill |first1=Allie |last2=Bloom |first2=Mike |date=May 8, 2021 |title='The Boys' Season 1 release date, trailer, cast, plot, renewal, and more |url=https://www.inverse.com/entertainment/55035-the-boys-release-date-trailer-cast-plot-spoilers-for-the-amazon-show |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231202162436/https://www.inverse.com/entertainment/55035-the-boys-release-date-trailer-cast-plot-spoilers-for-the-amazon-show |archive-date=December 2, 2023 |access-date=August 6, 2024 |website=[[Inverse (website)|Inverse]]}}</ref> episodes are released on a weekly basis with each season premiering its first three episodes for the remainder of the series.<ref>{{cite web |last=Shannon Miller |first=Liz |date=June 26, 2020 |title=Why It's Great News That 'The Boys' Season 2 Will Be Released Weekly |url=https://collider.com/the-boys-season-2-release-date-weekly/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230410012614/https://collider.com/the-boys-season-2-release-date-weekly/ |archive-date=April 10, 2023 |access-date=August 6, 2024 |website=[[Collider (website)|Collider]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Gelman |first=Vlada |date=January 7, 2022 |title='The Boys' Season 3 Gets Premiere Date — Watch Announcement Video |url=https://tvline.com/2022/01/07/the-boys-season-3-premiere-date-amazon-prime-video/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220107162005/https://tvline.com/2022/01/07/the-boys-season-3-premiere-date-amazon-prime-video/ |archive-date=January 7, 2022 |access-date=August 6, 2024 |website=[[TVLine]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Rice |first=Lynette |date=February 22, 2024 |title='The Boys': When to Expect Fourth Season Return |url=https://deadline.com/2024/02/the-boys-season-four-return-date-prime-video-1235833883/ |access-date=August 6, 2024 |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]}}</ref>

As of July 18, 2024, thirty-two episodes have aired throughout the course of four seasons. The series is currently set to conclude with a fifth and final season, announced on June 11, 2024, and currently in development.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2024/05/the-boys-renewed-season-5-amazon-1235914651/ |title='The Boys' Renewed for Season 5 at Amazon |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |last=Campione |first=Katie |date=May 14, 2024 |access-date=August 6, 2024}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Maas |first=Jennifer |date=June 11, 2024 |title='The Boys' to End with Season 5 on Amazon |url=https://variety.com/2024/tv/news/the-boys-season-5-final-season-1236033418/ |access-date=August 6, 2024 |website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/feature/the-boys-season-5-everything-we-know-1236014576/ |title='The Boys' Season 5: Everything We Know So Far |last=Gomez |first=Dessi |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |date=July 18, 2024 |access-date=August 6, 2024}}</ref> A companion short film, ''[[The Boys (franchise)#Butcher (2020)|Butcher: A Short Film]]'', was released on September 10, 2020.<ref name="Butcher">{{cite web |last=Weintraub |first=Steven |date=July 7, 2020 |title=Exclusive: Eric Kripke on 'The Boys' Season 2, Giancarlo Esposito's Role, and a Billy/William Butcher Short Film |url=https://collider.com/the-boys-season-2-details-eric-kripke-interview/ |access-date=August 6, 2024 |website=[[Collider (website)|Collider]]}}</ref>

