==Other media==
===''Seven on 7'' (2021–present)===
{{Main|Seven on 7}}

''Seven on 7'' is a [[wiktionary:faux|faux]] [[Current affairs (news format)|current affairs]] [[Web series|digital series]] serving as the center of several [[viral marketing]] campaigns for ''The Boys'' and its spin-off series ''[[Gen V]]''. As of September 28, 2022, a total of nine "minisodes" have been released.<ref>{{cite magazine |last=Romano |first=Nick |date=July 7, 2021 |title='The Boys' launches Vought News digital series to fill in story gaps ahead of Season 3 |url=https://ew.com/tv/the-boys-season-3-vought-news-network-digital-series |access-date=August 6, 2024 |magazine=[[Entertainment Weekly]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |date=July 7, 2021 |title='The Boys': Vought News Network – Seven on 7 with Cameron Coleman (July 2021) |url=https://www.ign.com/videos/the-boys-vought-news-network-seven-on-7-with-cameron-coleman-july-2021 |access-date=August 6, 2024 |website=[[IGN]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://screenrant.com/boys-show-vought-news-hughie-witch-hunt-video/ |title='The Boys' Vought News Video: Hughie is Interrogated Over Hero Witch Hunt |last=Woinski |first=Bart |website=[[Screen Rant]] |date=January 8, 2022 |access-date=August 6, 2024}}</ref>

===''Butcher: A Short Film'' (2020)===
{{Main|The Boys (franchise)#Butcher (2020)}}

A companion [[short film]], set between the [[The Boys season 1|first]] and [[The Boys season 2|second]] seasons of ''The Boys'', was uploaded on [[Twitter]] on September 10, 2020, alongside the release of the series episode "[[Nothing Like It in the World (The Boys episode)|Nothing Like It in the World]]", with [[Karl Urban]] reprising his role as [[Billy Butcher]].<ref name="Butcher"/><ref>{{cite tweet |user=TheBoysTV |number=1304076665274859522 |date=September 10, 2020 |title=Wondering what Butcher's been up to? Check out 'BUTCHER: A Short Film' while you wait for tomorrow's new episode 👀 |access-date=August 6, 2024}}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine |url=https://ew.com/tv/the-boys-short-film-karl-urban-season-2/ |title=Watch 'The Boys' Karl Urban-centric short film to fill in some of the Season 2 gaps |last=Romano |first=Nick |magazine=[[Entertainment Weekly]] |date=September 10, 2020 |access-date=August 6, 2024}}</ref>

